Maintainer: Nima Hejazi <nh@nimahejazi.org>
Description: Targeted maximum likelihood estimation (TMLE) of population-level
    causal effects under stochastic treatment regimes and related nonparametric
    variable importance analysis. Tools are provided for computing the TMLE of a
    treatment effect under interventions that are shifts of a continuous-valued
    treatment, as first described by I. Díaz Muñoz and M.J. van der Laan (2013;
    doi: <10.1111/j.1541-0420.2011.01685.x>) and expanded upon in I. Díaz and
    M.J. van der Laan (2018). This is an adapter package for use with the tmle3
    framework and the tlverse software ecosystem for Targeted Learning.
